  "prompt": "Why don't other AAP MLAs take anticipatory bail like Arvind Kejriwal ?",
  "response": "Arvind Kejriwal's decision to seek anticipatory bail may be based on his individual circumstances, legal strategy, and the specific charges he faces. Other Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) MLAs may choose not to pursue anticipatory bail for various reasons, including the nature of their legal situations, the advice of their legal counsel, or a belief that they are not at risk of arrest.\n\nEach case is unique, and legal strategies can vary significantly based on the details of the case, the evidence involved, and the perceived likelihood of arrest. Additionally, some MLAs might choose to address allegations directly without seeking anticipatory bail, depending on their confidence in their legal standing and the political context. \n\nUltimately, decisions regarding legal actions are influenced by personal, legal, and strategic considerations that can differ from one individual to another.",
